                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pr7nf04/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>as your agent requested the talented Minister<lb/> to furnish me a copy for your\n                Magazine<lb/> I addressed him a note on the subject<lb/> last evening but no reply\n                yet received<lb/> should the he comply I shall immediately<lb/> forward it to you\n                    <add>?</add> delivers extempore<lb/> it may be some few days ere I obtain<lb/>\n                it or his refusal as If I must ask<add>?</add> not<lb/> He does not care about\n                publishing his<lb/> sermonsâ€”after the services were concluded<lb/> nearly the whole\n                of His Congregation &amp; many<lb/> of the <placeName>Rampart St</placeName>\n                Synagogue paid their<lb/> respects to him at his splendidly furnished<lb/> Dwelling\n                    <sic>anexd</sic> to the Synagogue. The House<lb/> was brilliantly lit up with\n                Gas &amp; mine Host<lb/> not unprepared for his Guests, who one &amp; all<lb/> did\n                full Justice to the plentiful supply<lb/> of <sic>champaigne</sic> &amp; other good\n                things <del>?</del><lb/> Take it in all it was an event that will<lb/> live long in\n                pleasant memory to all who<lb/> were so fortunate as to be present The officers<lb/>\n                of the Congregation deserve much credit<lb/> for the credible manner in which\n                every<lb/> thing was arranged &amp; carried out</p>\n            <p>I noticed among the audience a large number<lb/> of our Oldest citizens with their\n                families<lb/> of our course <persName>Mr Sheppard</persName> the old friend of<lb/>\n                the late <persName>Judah Touro</persName> was among the rest<lb/> nothing further to\n                add but remain</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\">Yours Truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Isaac Hart</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pr7nf04/canvas/p2"
